    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Mesoamerican religious structures in central Mexico, usually a terraced pyramid surmounted by a temple; other types of structures such as tzompantli, cuauhxicalco, and calmecac. Literally, "teotl (deity) house."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
